 P(X\geqslant w)=1-\frac{\Gamma(w,\lambda)}{\Gamma(w)}. 
 \begin{align} P(X\geqslant w)&=\frac{\Gamma(w)-\Gamma(w,\lambda)}{\Gamma(w)}=\frac{1}{\Gamma(w)}\left(\int_0^\infty t^{w-1}e^{-t}\,\mathrm dt-\int_\lambda^\infty t^{w-1}e^{-t}\,\mathrm dt\right)\\ &=\frac{1}{\Gamma(w)}\int_0^\lambda t^{w-1}e^{-t}\,\mathrm dt=P(Y\leqslant\lambda). \end{align} 
